      {
        "id": "urn:oid:2.49.0.1.840.0.83de1d7fcd7a7cc55999dee29af9d0e7c60563aa.001.1",
        "event": "Special Weather Statement",
        "headline": "Special Weather Statement issued April 9 at 8:15AM AKDT by NWS Fairbanks AK",
        "description": "Gusty winds Thursday from St. Lawrence Island through the Bering\nStrait coincide with a front that brings 1 to 2 inches of snow to\nthe area through Thursday. Southerly wind gusts through the\nBering Strait up to 60 mph are possible, affecting Wales and\nDiomede most strongly. Gusts up to 45 mph are possible across St.\nLawrence Island. Weaker gusts are expected further east on the\nSeward Peninsula for Teller, Brevig Mission, and Shishmaref.\n\nAnother round of precipitation is expected to begin Frida",
        "severity": "Moderate",
